fields.value: Replication Data for: Lookit (Part 2): Assessing the Viability of Online Developmental Research, Results from Three Case Studies

dsDescriptionValue.value: Open Mind: Discoveries in Cognitive Science Forthcoming.

fields.value: Note: All videos are from sessions where parents chose a privacy level of “free” and confirmed that publicity and educational use of the video are acceptable.

files.description: An example session from Study 1. The bottom panel shows the participant video collected; the top panel shows the stimuli this child was viewing at the time (reconstructed based on the condition, not recorded directly). Clips are labeled in the top left corner; the first four clips are practice trials and the last four clips are test trials.

files.description: An example session from Study 2. The bottom panel shows the participant video collected; the top panel shows the stimuli this child was viewing at the time (reconstructed based on the condition, not recorded directly). Clips are labeled in the top left corner. Clips 1, 5, and 10 are calibration trials; 2, 3, 4, 6, 7, and 8 are practice trials; 9 is the dialogue introducing the new verb; and 11, 12, and 13 are test trials.
